# Jeopardy Game Telegram Bot - Project Context

## Technology Stack
- Python 3.10+
- asyncio, aiohttp for Telegram API communication
- PostgreSQL (asyncpg or SQLAlchemy)
- Pure Telegram API (no aiogram or other libraries)
- RabbitMQ (optional, for message queue)
- Docker, docker-compose

## Bot Architecture (from Habr article)
- **Poller** (single instance) - receives updates from Telegram, puts them into queue
- **Worker** (multiple instances) - takes tasks from queue, executes business logic
- **Shared asyncio.Queue** for poller -> workers communication
- **TgClient** - class for Telegram API methods (getUpdates, sendMessage, etc.)

## Database Entities
```sql
-- User
- id: BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY
- telegram_id: BIGINT UNIQUE NOT NULL
- username: VARCHAR(255)
- created_at: TIMESTAMP

-- Game
- id: UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
- chat_id: BIGINT NOT NULL
- status: VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'waiting'  -- waiting, active, finished
- current_player_id: UUID REFERENCES participant(id)
- host_id: UUID REFERENCES user(id)
- created_at: TIMESTAMP
- finished_at: TIMESTAMP

-- Participant
- id: UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
- user_id: UUID REFERENCES user(id)
- game_id: UUID REFERENCES game(id)
- score: INTEGER DEFAULT 0
- joined_at: TIMESTAMP
- is_active: BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE
- UNIQUE(game_id, user_id)

-- Topic
- id: UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
- title: TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE

-- Question
- id: UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
- topic_id: UUID REFERENCES topic(id)
- text: TEXT NOT NULL
- answer: TEXT NOT NULL
- cost: INTEGER NOT NULL CHECK (cost > 0)

-- QuestionInGame
- id: UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
- game_id: UUID REFERENCES game(id)
- question_id: UUID REFERENCES question(id)
- status: VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'pending'  -- pending, asked, answered
- asked_by: UUID REFERENCES participant(id)
- answered_by: UUID REFERENCES participant(id)
- asked_at: TIMESTAMP
- answered_at: TIMESTAMP
- UNIQUE(game_id, question_id)

-- GameState
- id: UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
- game_id: UUID UNIQUE REFERENCES game(id)
- status: VARCHAR(20)  -- choosing_question, waiting_buzzer, waiting_answer, paused
- current_question_id: UUID REFERENCES question_in_game(id)
- buzzer_pressed_by: UUID REFERENCES participant(id)
- buzzer_pressed_at: TIMESTAMP
- timer_ends_at: TIMESTAMP
- updated_at: TIMESTAMP

TG BOT COMMANDS

Command           Description                      Access
/start            Create new game or join existing Everyone
/join             Join game as player              Everyone
/leave            Leave current game               Everyone
/spectate         Become spectator                 Everyone
/start_game       Start the game                   Host only
/stop             Stop game prematurely            Host only
/score            Show current score in this game  Everyone
/rules            Game rules                       Everyone
/help             List all commands                Everyone
/answer <text>    Submit answer                    Player who pressed buzzer
/buzzer           answer button                    All players
/add_topic <name> Create new topic                 Host only
/add_question     Add question (step by step)      Host only
/remove_question <id> Delete question              Host only
/remove_topic <id>    Delete topic                 Host only
/pause            Pause game                       Host only
/resume           Resume game                      Host only


Game Flow Logic
Lobby (status = waiting)

After /start, game created, first user becomes host

Players join via /join

Host presses /start_game → transition to active

Game Start

Random current_player selected from participants

QuestionInGame records created for all questions (status = pending)

Transition to choosing_question state

Question Selection (choosing_question)

Bot shows board: topics + costs of unanswered questions

Only current_player can select

On selection: QuestionInGame.status = asked, asked_by = current_player

Bot asks question, transition to waiting_buzzer, 10 sec timer

Waiting for Buzzer (waiting_buzzer)

All players can press /buzzer

First to press: buzzer_pressed_by = this player, transition to waiting_answer, 15 sec timer

Timeout (10 sec): "No one pressed. Correct answer: X", question burns (answered without answerer), return to choosing_question

Waiting for Answer (waiting_answer)

Only buzzer_pressed_by can send /answer

Correct: +cost to score, QuestionInGame.answered_by = player, current_player = answerer

Wrong: -cost from score, question burns, current_player unchanged

Timeout (15 sec): question burns, current_player unchanged

Return to choosing_question (if questions remain)

Game End

All QuestionInGame have status = answered

Show leaderboard (sorted by score)

Game.status = finished

